GIT:

touch file
cat file
vim file
rm file or rm -rf file or folder
mkdir folder
rmdir folder
rm -rf folder
cd folder
cd ..
history
clear
git clone url
git add .
git commit -m "add any commit"
git push
git init or git checkout -b "master"
git add .
git commit -m "add any commit"
git remote add origin url
git push origin master
cp file folder
mv file folder


MAVEN:

mvn archetype:generate
mvn clean
mvn compile
mvn test
mvn package
mvn install
mvn deploy

JENKINS:

CI-CD: continous integration & continous deployment
continous integration: means installing the plugins from manage jenkins to run
continous deployment: means deploying or delivering the work with the help of installed pluggins
 pipelines:

 declarative, scripted

SONARQUBES: it's a testing tool, to check if there is any bugs, vulnerabilities etc..

DOCKER:

yum install docker -y
sudo service docker start
docker images
docker ps
docker ps -a
docker pull image
docker run -it --name (container name) (image name)
docker start container id
docker stop container id
docker run -it p8080:8080 image name  or docker exec -it --name (container name) -p8080:8080 image name_container


TERRAFORM:

it's an autimation tool and terraform can be used to create a resources by writing the codes or by commands
it's file refers to  .tf

terraform commands:

terraform init
terraform plan
terraform validate
terraform apply

